The Busia administration will introduce energy-saving Improved cook stoves. &ldquo;Two to three pieces of firewood can be used in the improved stoves, compared to the amount used with the [traditional] three stones,&rdquo; Energy executive Bernard Yaite said on Wednesday.The department will partner with German Energising Development. &ldquo;Residents should look on long-term expenditure and realise that modern energy is less costly,&rdquo; Yaite said . GIZ EnDev cluster manager Everlyne Minikhu said the programme targets to provide clean modern energy.&ldquo;Jiko kisasa and Roket stoves save up to 40 and 50 per cent of fuel, respectively,&rdquo; she said.